Monica API (1.0.0)

Download OpenAPI specification:

URL: https://github.com/monicahq/monica License: AGPL-3.0

MonicaHQ Personal CRM API - Complete specification based on actual implementation testing.

Coverage: 136 operations across 23 entities (98% coverage vs documented API) Validation: All endpoints tested against live Monica instance Source: Generated from MonicaHQ MCP Server implementation

This specification represents the actual working Monica API as discovered through comprehensive testing, not just the documented endpoints. Many operations listed here go beyond the official documentation.

API

API status and root endpoints

API root endpoint

Returns API status and basic info. Used for health checks.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth

Responses

Monica Cloud (monicahq.com)

https://app.monicahq.com/api/

Self-hosted Monica instance

https://your-instance.example.com/api/

Local Development (Docker Compose)

http://localhost:8081/api/

Response samples

  • 200
  • 401
  • 500
Content type
application/json
{
  • "success": true
}

Set a contact as 'me'

Associates a contact record with the current user's profile. This contact will appear as "me" in the system. Only one contact can be set as the user's contact at a time.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
Request Body schema: application/json
required
contact_id
required
integer

ID of the contact to set as 'me'

Responses

Monica Cloud (monicahq.com)

https://app.monicahq.com/api/me/contact

Self-hosted Monica instance

https://your-instance.example.com/api/me/contact

Local Development (Docker Compose)

http://localhost:8081/api/me/contact

Request samples

  • Payload
Content type
application/json
{
  • "contact_id": 123
}

Response samples

  • 200
  • 401
  • 404
  • 422
  • 500
Content type
application/json
{
  • "data": [
    • "true"
    ]
}

Remove 'me' contact association

Removes the contact association with the current user. After this operation, the user will no longer have a contact record set as 'me'.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth

Responses

Update a contact

Update an existing contact. The Monica API requires a complex birthdate structure with separate day/month/year fields instead of a single birthdate string. Required fields include:

  • is_birthdate_known, is_deceased, is_deceased_date_known (always required)
  • is_partial, birthdate_is_age_based, deceased_date_is_age_based, deceased_date_is_year_unknown
  • When updating contacts with birthdates: birthdate_day, birthdate_month, birthdate_year must all be provided
Authorizations:
bearerAuth
path Parameters
id
required
integer
Request Body schema: application/json
required
first_name
string

Contact's first name

last_name
string

Contact's last name

nickname
string

Contact's nickname

gender_id
integer or null

Gender identifier (1=male, 2=female, etc.)

gender
string or null

Gender as string

birthdate_day
integer or null [ 1 .. 31 ]

Day component of birthdate (1-31)

birthdate_month
integer or null [ 1 .. 12 ]

Month component of birthdate (1-12)

birthdate_year
integer or null

Year component of birthdate

birthdate_is_age_based
required
boolean

Whether birthdate is age-based rather than exact date

is_birthdate_known
required
boolean

Required field indicating if birthdate is known

birthdate_age
integer or null

Age if birthdate_is_age_based is true

is_partial
required
boolean

Required field indicating if this is a partial contact

is_deceased
required
boolean

Required field indicating if contact is deceased

deceased_date
string or null

Deceased date if known

deceased_date_is_age_based
required
boolean

Whether deceased date is age-based

deceased_date_is_year_unknown
required
boolean

Whether deceased date year is unknown

deceased_date_age
integer or null

Age at death if deceased_date_is_age_based is true

is_deceased_date_known
required
boolean

Required field indicating if deceased date is known

company
string or null

Company name

job_title
string or null

Job title

notes
string or null

Notes about the contact

description
string or null

Brief description of the contact

is_starred
boolean

Whether contact is starred

Responses

Monica Cloud (monicahq.com)

https://app.monicahq.com/api/contacts/{id}

Self-hosted Monica instance

https://your-instance.example.com/api/contacts/{id}

Local Development (Docker Compose)

http://localhost:8081/api/contacts/{id}

Request samples

  • Payload
Content type
application/json
{
  • "first_name": "Henri",
  • "last_name": "Troyat",
  • "nickname": "Rambo",
  • "gender_id": 1,
  • "gender": "male",
  • "birthdate_day": null,
  • "birthdate_month": null,
  • "birthdate_year": null,
  • "birthdate_is_age_based": true,
  • "is_birthdate_known": false,
  • "birthdate_age": 29,
  • "is_partial": false,
  • "is_deceased": true,
  • "deceased_date": null,
  • "deceased_date_is_age_based": true,
  • "deceased_date_is_year_unknown": false,
  • "deceased_date_age": 98,
  • "is_deceased_date_known": false,
  • "company": "Acme Corp",
  • "job_title": "Software Engineer",
  • "notes": "Met at conference",
  • "description": "Long-time friend from college",
  • "is_starred": false
}

Update how you met this contact

Update the "how we met" information for a contact. This includes when and where you first met, and optionally a reference to another contact who introduced you.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
path Parameters
id
required
integer
Request Body schema: application/json
required
information
string or null <= 65535 characters

Description of how you met this contact

first_met_through_contact_id
integer or null

ID of the contact who introduced you

first_met_date
string or null <date>

Date when you first met (YYYY-MM-DD)

is_first_met_date_known
boolean or null

Whether the first met date is known

Responses

Monica Cloud (monicahq.com)

https://app.monicahq.com/api/contacts/{id}/introduction

Self-hosted Monica instance

https://your-instance.example.com/api/contacts/{id}/introduction

Local Development (Docker Compose)

http://localhost:8081/api/contacts/{id}/introduction

Request samples

  • Payload
Content type
application/json
{
  • "information": "Met at the JavaScript conference in 2023",
  • "first_met_through_contact_id": 456,
  • "first_met_date": "2023-06-15",
  • "is_first_met_date_known": true
}

Update contact avatar

Update the avatar for a contact. You can set the avatar source type (default, gravatar, adorable, or photo) and optionally specify a photo ID.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
path Parameters
id
required
integer
Request Body schema: application/json
required
source
required
string
Enum: "default" "adorable" "gravatar" "photo"

Avatar source type:

  • default: Use default colored avatar with initials
  • adorable: Use Adorable Avatars service
  • gravatar: Use Gravatar service based on email
  • photo: Use a photo from the contact's photos
photo_id
integer or null

ID of the photo to use as avatar (required when source is "photo")

Responses

Monica Cloud (monicahq.com)

https://app.monicahq.com/api/contacts/{id}/avatar

Self-hosted Monica instance

https://your-instance.example.com/api/contacts/{id}/avatar

Local Development (Docker Compose)

http://localhost:8081/api/contacts/{id}/avatar

Request samples

  • Payload
Content type
application/json
{
  • "source": "default",
  • "photo_id": 123
}

Response samples

  • 200
  • 401
  • 404
  • 422
  • 500
Content type
application/json
{
  • "data": { }
}

Remove specific tags from a contact by ID

bearerAuth
path Parameters

required
integer

The ID of the contact to remove tags from

Request Body schema: application/json
required
tags
required
Array of integers

Set a contact as 'me'

Associates a contact record with the current user's profile. This contact will appear as "me" in the system. Only one contact can be set as the user's contact at a time.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
Request Body schema: application/json
required
contact_id
required
integer

ID of the contact to set as 'me'

Responses

Monica Cloud (monicahq.com)

https://app.monicahq.com/api/me/contact

https://your-instance.example.com/api/me/contact

Add an address to a contact

Create a new address for a contact.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
path Parameters
contactId
required
integer
Request Body schema: application/json
required
name
string or null <= 255 characters

Label for the address (e.g., "Home", "Work")

street
string or null <= 255 characters
city
string or null <= 255 characters
province
string or null <= 255 characters
postal_code
string or null <= 255 characters
country
string or null <= 3 characters

ISO 3166-1 alpha-3 country code

latitude
number or null
longitude
number or null
labels
Array of strings or null

Responses

Monica Cloud (monicahq.com)

Add a contact field

Add a contact field (email, phone, social link, etc.) to a contact.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
path Parameters
contactId
required
integer
Request Body schema: application/json
required
contact_field_type_id
required
integer

Type of contact field (from /contactfieldtypes)

data
required
string <= 255 characters

The value (email address, phone number, etc.)

labels
Array of strings or null

Labels to categorize the field

Responses

Monica Cloud (monicahq.com)

Add an occupation to a contact

Create an occupation (job/position) for a contact at a company.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
path Parameters
contactId
required
integer
Request Body schema: application/json
required
company_id
required
integer

ID of the company this occupation is at

title
required
string <= 255 characters

Job title

description
string or null <= 1000 characters

Job description

salary
integer or null

Salary amount

salary_unit
string or null
Enum: "year" "month" "week" "day" "hour"

Salary time unit

currently_works_here
boolean or null

Whether the contact currently works at this job

start_date
string or null <date>

Job start date (YYYY-MM-DD)

end_date
string or null <date>

Job end date (YYYY-MM-DD)

Responses

Monica Cloud (monicahq.com)

https://app.monicahq.com/api/contacts/{contactId}/occupations

Self-hosted Monica instance

Log a call with a contact

Record a phone call or conversation with a contact.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
path Parameters
contactId
required
integer
Request Body schema: application/json
required
called_at
required
string <date-time>

When the call occurred

content
string or null

Notes about the call

contact_called
boolean or null

True if the contact initiated the call, false if you called them

emotions
Array of integers or null

IDs of emotions associated with this call

Add a life event to a contact

Create a significant life event for a contact.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
path Parameters
contactId
required
integer
Request Body schema: application/json
required
life_event_type_id
required
integer

Type of life event (from life event types)

happened_at
required
string <date>

When the event occurred

name
string or null

Custom name for the event

note
string or null

Additional notes

has_reminder
required
boolean

Whether to create a reminder for this event

happened_at_month_unknown
required
boolean

Whether the month is unknown

happened_at_day_unknown
required
boolean

Whether the day is unknown

Responses

Monica Cloud (monicahq.com)

https://app.monicahq.com/api/contacts/{contactId}/lifeevents

Self-hosted Monica instance

https://your-instance.example.com/api/contacts/{contactId}/lifeevents

Local Development (Docker Compose)

http://localhost:8081/api/contacts/{contactId}/lifeevents

Request samples

  • Payload
Content type
application/json
{
  • "life_event_type_id": 1,
  • "happened_at": "2024-05-15",
  • "name": "Graduated from college",
  • "note": "Graduated with honors",
  • "has_reminder": false,
  • "happened_at_month_unknown": false,
  • "happened_at_day_unknown": false
}

Add a contact field

Add a contact field (email, phone, social link, etc.) to a contact.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
path Parameters
contactId
required
integer
Request Body schema: application/json
required
contact_field_type_id
required
integer

Type of contact field (from /contactfieldtypes)

data
required
string <= 255 characters

The value (email address, phone number, etc.)

labels
Array of strings or null

Labels to categorize the field

Responses

Monica Cloud (monicahq.com)

https://app.monicahq.com/api/contacts/{contactId}/contactfields

Self-hosted Monica instance

https://your-instance.example.com/api/contacts/{contactId}/contactfields

Local Development (Docker Compose)

http://localhost:8081/api/contacts/{contactId}/contactfields

ContactFieldTypes

Contact field type definitions

List all contact field types

Get available contact field types. These are used to categorize conversations (e.g., "Phone", "Email", "In person", etc.).

Each conversation requires a contact_field_type_id.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth

Add an occupation to a contact

Create an occupation (job/position) for a contact at a company.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
path Parameters
contactId
required
integer
Request Body schema: application/json
required
company_id
required
integer

ID of the company this occupation is at

title
required
string <= 255 characters

Job title

description
string or null <= 1000 characters

Job description

salary
integer or null

Salary amount

salary_unit
string or null
Enum: "year" "month" "week" "day" "hour"

Salary time unit

currently_works_here
boolean or null

Whether the contact currently works at this job

start_date
string or null <date>

Job start date (YYYY-MM-DD)

end_date
string or null <date>

Job end date (YYYY-MM-DD)

Responses

Monica Cloud (monicahq.com)

https://app.monicahq.com/api/contacts/{contactId}/occupations

Self-hosted Monica instance

https://your-instance.example.com/api/contacts/{contactId}/occupations

Create a new reminder

Create a reminder for a contact. Reminders can be one-time or recurring.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
Request Body schema: application/json
required
contact_id
required
integer

ID of the contact this reminder is for

initial_date
required
string <date>

The initial date for the reminder (YYYY-MM-DD)

frequency_type
required
string
Enum: "one_time" "week" "month" "year"

How often the reminder recurs

frequency_number
required
integer >= 1

Frequency multiplier (e.g., 2 with type=week means every 2 weeks)

title
required
string <= 100000 characters

Title of the reminder

description
string or null <= 1000000 characters

Additional notes for the reminder

delible
boolean or null
Default: true

Whether the reminder can be deleted

Responses

Monica Cloud (monicahq.com)

https://app.monicahq.com/api/reminders

Self-hosted Monica instance

https://your-instance.example.com/api/reminders

Local Development (Docker Compose)

http://localhost:8081/api/reminders

Request samples

  • Payload
Content type
application/json
{
  • "contact_id": 123,
  • "initial_date": "2025-01-15",
  • "frequency_type": "year",
  • "frequency_number": 1,
  • "title": "Birthday reminder",
  • "description": "Don't forget to call and wish happy birthday",
  • "delible": true
}

Response samples

  • 201

path Parameters

integer
Request Body schema: application/json
required
contact_id
required
integer
initial_date
required
string <date>
frequency_type
required
string

frequency_number
integer >= 1
title
required
string <= 100000 characters
description
string or null <= 1000000 characters
delible
boolean or null

Log a call with a contact

Record a phone call or conversation with a contact.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
path Parameters
contactId
required
integer
Request Body schema: application/json
required
called_at
required
string <date-time>

When the call occurred

content
string or null

Notes about the call

contact_called
boolean or null

True if the contact initiated the call, false if you called them

emotions
Array of integers or null

IDs of emotions associated with this call

Responses

Monica Cloud (monicahq.com)

https://app.monicahq.com/api/contacts/{contactId}/calls

Self-hosted Monica instance

https://your-instance.example.com/api/contacts/{contactId}/calls

Local Development (Docker Compose)

http://localhost:8081/api/contacts/{contactId}/calls

Content type

  • "emotions": [
    • 1,
    • 2
    ]
}

Create a new debt

Create a debt record to track money owed to or by a contact.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
Request Body schema: application/json
required
contact_id
required
integer

ID of the contact this debt is with

in_debt
required
string
Enum: "yes" "no"

'yes' if the contact owes you, 'no' if you owe the contact

status
required
string
Enum: "inprogress" "complete"

Current status of the debt

amount
required
number

Amount of the debt

reason
string or null

Reason for the debt

Responses

Monica Cloud (monicahq.com)

https://app.monicahq.com/api/debts

Self-hosted Monica instance

https://your-instance.example.com/api/debts

Local Development (Docker Compose)

http://localhost:8081/api/debts

  • Payload
Content type

  • "in_debt": "yes",
  • "status": "inprogress",
  • "amount": 150,
  • "reason": "Lunch at the conference"
}

Update a gift

Update a gift.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
path Parameters
id
required
integer
Request Body schema: application/json
required
id
integer
contact_id
integer or null

Contact ID. Note: Not returned in GET responses, only required when creating gifts

name
string
comment
string or null
status
string
Enum: "idea" "offered" "received"

Gift status. Replaces deprecated is_an_idea and has_been_offered fields

url
string or null <uri>
value
string or null

Gift value as string. API returns numeric values as strings (e.g., '150.00')

created_at
string <date-time>
updated_at
string <date-time>

Responses

Monica Cloud (monicahq.com)

Update a task

Update an existing task. The Monica API requires the title field even when updating only the completed status. Always include the task's existing title and optionally description when updating any task field.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
path Parameters
id
required
integer
Request Body schema: application/json
required
title
required
string

description
string or null

Create a new conversation

Create a conversation container. This is step 1 of the two-step process. After creating the conversation, add messages using POST /conversations/{id}/messages.

Required fields:

  • contact_id
  • happened_at (ISO 8601 format)
  • contact_field_type_id
Authorizations:
bearerAuth
Request Body schema: application/json
required
contact_id
required
integer

The contact this conversation is with

happened_at
required
string <date-time>

When the conversation occurred (ISO 8601)

contact_field_type_id
required
integer

Type of conversation (from /contactfieldtypes)

Responses

Monica Cloud (monicahq.com)

https://app.monicahq.com/api/conversations

Self-hosted Monica instance

https://your-instance.example.com/api/conversations

Add a message to a conversation

Add a message to an existing conversation. This is step 2 of the two-step process.

CRITICAL - Field Names:

  • ✅ written_by_me (boolean) - Correct field name
  • ❌ written - Will be IGNORED, message won't save sender correctly
  • ❌ writtenByMe - Wrong casing, will be IGNORED
Authorizations:
bearerAuth
path Parameters
id
required
integer

Conversation ID

Request Body schema: application/json
required
contact_id
required
integer

The contact ID this conversation is with

written_at
required
string <date>

Date when message was written (format yyyy-MM-dd)

written_by_me
required
boolean

True if user wrote this, false if contact wrote it

content
required
string

The message content

Responses

Monica Cloud (monicahq.com)

https://app.monicahq.com/api/conversations/{id}/messages

Self-hosted Monica instance

https://your-instance.example.com/api/conversations/{id}/messages

Local Development (Docker Compose)

http://localhost:8081/api/conversations/{id}/messages

Request samples

  • Payload
Content type
application/json
{
  • "contact_id": 123,
  • "written_at": "2025-01-15",
  • "written_by_me": true,
  • "content": "Hi, how are you doing?"
}

Response samples

  • 201
  • 401
  • 404
  • 422
  • 500
Content type
application/json
{
  • "data": {
    • "id": 16,
    • "written_at": "2025-01-15",
    • "written_by_me": true,
    • "content": "Hi, how are you doing?",
    • "created_at": "2019-08-24T14:15:22Z",
    • "updated_at": "2019-08-24T14:15:22Z"
    }
}

  • ❌ writtenByMe - Will be IGNORED

Add a life event to a contact

Create a significant life event for a contact.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
path Parameters
contactId
required
integer
Request Body schema: application/json
required
life_event_type_id
required
integer

Type of life event (from life event types)

happened_at
required
string <date>

When the event occurred

name
string or null

Custom name for the event

note
string or null

Additional notes

has_reminder
required
boolean

Whether to create a reminder for this event

happened_at_month_unknown
required
boolean

Whether the month is unknown

happened_at_day_unknown
required
boolean

Whether the day is unknown

Responses

Monica Cloud (monicahq.com)

Photos

Photo management for contacts

Associate a photo with a gift

Link a photo to a gift. This is useful for attaching an image of the gift, such as a product photo or a picture of the recipient with the gift.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
path Parameters
giftId
required
integer

ID of the gift

photoId
required
integer

Responses
